–Afdød","1150–Female":"1150–Afdød","1166–1198":"1166–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Afdød","1182–1258":"1182–1258","1176–1239":"1176–1239","1198–1247":"1198–1247","1128–1207":"1128–1207","–1203":"–1203","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1182":"1182","1239":"1239","1128":"1128","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","1178":"1178","Abt 1198":"omkring 1198","1166":"1166","1207":"1207","Addington, Surrey, England":"Addington, Surrey, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1171–":"1171–Overleden","1150–Female":"1150–Overleden","1166–1198":"1166–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Overleden","1182–1258":"1182–1258","1176–1239":"1176–1239","1198–1247":"1198–1247","1128–1207":"1128–1207","–1203":"–1203","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1182":"1182","1239":"1239","1128":"1128","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","1178":"1178","Abt 1198":"circa 1198","1166":"1166","1207":"1207","Addington, Surrey, England":"Addington, Surrey, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1171–":"1171–Deceased","1150–Female":"1150–Deceased","1166–1198":"1166–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Deceased","1182–1258":"1182–1258","1176–1239":"1176–1239","1198–1247":"1198–1247","1128–1207":"1128–1207","–1203":"–1203","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1182":"1182","1239":"1239","1128":"1128","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","1178":"1178","Abt 1198":"about 1198","1166":"1166","1207":"1207","Addington, Surrey, England":"Addington, Surrey, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Cheng, Jing, Kam Fung, Wai Shing, Wing, Yali, Yuk.","Chinese:","variant Romanization of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ou","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ying, Ching, Heng, Hong, Jia, Kuang Yu, Li-Ching, Cho, Chong, Chung, Sa.  Southeast Asian Lichun, Ming, Quan, Roeun, Sokhom, Chau, Hai, Leang, Ly, Nhanh, Phan, Pho, Tha.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 歐, meaning ‘to sing someone's praise’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the placename Dong Ou (東甌), a fief (in present-day Wenzhou in Zhejiang province) which was granted to Yao in 192  BC . It is said that Yao was a descendant of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (ii) from the placename Ou Yu (歐餘), the name of a fief (located in present-day Zhejiang province) that was granted to Ti, the second son of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 區, originally denoting an ancient vessel for measurement in ancient Chinese: from the personal name of <i>Ou Zhizi</i> (歐治子), an expert sword-maker who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). Some of his descendants inherited <i>Ou</i> (歐) as their surname, simplifying the Chinese character 歐 to 區."]}]},{"name":"London","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone who came from London or a nickname for someone who had made a trip to London or had some other connection with the city. In some cases however, the Jewish name was purely artificial. The placename, recorded by the Roman historian Tacitus in the Latinized form <i>Londinium</i>, is obscure in origin and meaning, but may be derived from pre-Celtic (Old European) roots with a meaning something like ‘place at the navigable or unfordable river’."],"variants":[{"name":"Lonon","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   London  . This surname is very rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Lundon","meanings":["English: variant of   London  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret FitzPeter of London was born in 1171, in London, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Lord Peter Fitz Henry and Isabel De Chesney. She had at least 1 son with Ralph de Clere II."},"et":{"1171–":"1171–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1166–1198":"1166–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Surnud","1182–1258":"1182–1258","1176–1239":"1176–1239","1198–1247":"1198–1247","1128–1207":"1128–1207","–1203":"–1203","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1182":"1182","1239":"1239","1128":"1128","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","1178":"1178","Abt 1198":"umbes 1198","1166":"1166","1207":"1207","Addington, Surrey, England":"Addington, Surrey, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1171–":"1171–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1166–1198":"1166–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Kuollut","1182–1258":"1182–1258","1176–1239":"1176–1239","1198–1247":"1198–1247","1128–1207":"1128–1207","–1203":"–1203","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1182":"1182","1239":"1239","1128":"1128","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","1178":"1178","Abt 1198":"noin 1198","1166":"1166","1207":"1207","Addington, Surrey, England":"Addington, Surrey, England","Lincolns